Step_Description.Step_Description_label: Prepare test
Create artefact directories : D:\temp\1, D:\temp\2, D:\temp\3, D:\temp\4
Launch the Orchestra Framework
Create new admin context "C1"
Add new FileSystem Environment to ArtefactPath variable and set it to directory "d:\temp\1"
Add new FileSystem Environment to ArtefactPath variable and set it to directory "d:\temp\2"
Save context
Create new admin context "C2"
Add new FileSystem Environment to ArtefactPath variable and set it to directory "d:\temp\3"
Add new FileSystem Environment to ArtefactPath variable and set it to directory "d:\temp\4"
Save context
Test of the "GetLoadedContexts" command
Launch an "Execute" command from Start menu
Type command "orchestra:GetContextEnvironments://FrameworkCommands/FC" and press "Ok" to execute

Step_ExpectedResult.Step_ExpectedResult_label: The path to command status file "GetLoadedContexts_status.status" has been displayed in the console of the Orchestra Framework

Step_Description.Step_Description_label: Open the "GetLoadedContexts_status.status" file in a text editor

The status file looks like the following (Values depending on the test environment are displayed in red)
